ute, IN, US (02).jpg|100px]]\n|\n|\n|\n| [[Samuel Hannaford]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Iowa==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! width=\"10%\" | Building\n! width=\"10%\" | Location\n! width=\"5%\" | Image\n! width=\"15%\" | Sculpture\n! width=\"10%\" | Sculptor\n! width=\"10%\" | Architect\n! width=\"5%\" | Installed\n! width=\"10%\" | Medium\n! width=\"25%\" | Notes\n|-\n|[[Iowa State Capitol]]\n|[[Des Moines, Iowa|Des Moines]]\n|[[File:Des Moines Iowa 20090110 State Capitol Statue.JPG|100px]]East facade\n|East pediment:<br>West pediment:\n|\n|[[John C. Cochrane]]<br>[[Alfred H. Piquenard]]\n|1886\n|sandstone\n|[[File:Iowa State House; Des Moines, Iowa; June 30, 2013.JPG|100px|right]]West facade:\n|-\n|[[Dubuque County Courthouse]]\n|720 Central Avenue,<br>[[Dubuque, Iowa|Dubuque]]\n|[[File:DETAIL OF ARCH AND PEDIMENT OF WEST FACADE - Dubuque County Courthouse, 720 Central Avenue, Dubuque, Dubuque County, IA HABS IOWA,31-DUBU,5-6.tif|100px]]\n|West facade: Eagle pediment\n|\n|[[Fridolin Heer]] & Son\n|1891\n|\n|[[File:Dubuque County Courthouse.jpg|100px|right]]Painted zinc sculptures adorn the roof:\n|- \n|[[University of Iowa Museum of Natural History|Macbride Hall]]\n|[[University of Iowa]],<br>17 North Clinton Street,<br>[[Iowa City, Iowa|Iowa City]]\n|[[File:Iowa Hall.JPG|100px]]\n|A buffalo stands flanked by two elk\n|Sinclair Shearer<ref>{{cite web|title=Macbride Hall|url=https://mnh.uiowa.edu/macbride-hall|website=University of Iowa|accessdate=1 December 2016}}</ref>\n|[[Proudfoot & Bird]]\n|1908\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Greene County Courthouse (Iowa)|Greene County Courthouse]]\n|114 North Chestnut Street,<br>[[Jefferson, Iowa|Jefferson]]\n|[[File:GreeneCountyCourthouse.jpg|100px]]\n|\n|\n|[[Proudfoot, Bird & Rawson]]\n|1918\n|\n|\n|-\n|First Newton National Bank\n|100 N 2nd Avenue West,<br>[[Newton, Iowa|Newton]]\n|\n|a central figure of agricultural plenty is surrounded by four other figures and farm scenes in low relief<ref>{{cite web|title=First Newton National Ban