ect Benjamin Latrobe's 1819 elevation of the Cabildo], from Historic New Orleans Collection.</ref> This was replaced in 1822 by an American eagle flanked by cannons, by Cardelli.<ref>Patricia Heintzelman (June 30, 1975) {{NHLS url|id=66000373|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory-Nomination: The Cabildo}}, National Park Service and {{NHLS url|id=66000373|title=Accompanying 2 photos, exterior, from 1968.|photos=y}}</ref>\n|-\n\n|[[Gallier Hall]]<br>(New Orleans City Hall)\n|545 St. Charles Avenue,<br>[[New Orleans]]\n|[[File:CBD11Oct07GallierHallFront.jpg|100px]]\n|figures of ''Liberty, Justice'', and ''Commerce''<ref>{{cite web|title=Gallier Hall|url=http://www.knowla.org/entry/575/|website=Encyclopedia of Louisiana|accessdate=26 November 2016}}</ref>\n|R.E. Launitz \n|[[James Gallier]]\n|1851\n|white marble\n|[[File:CBD11Oct07GallierHallLibertyCapScales.jpg|100px|right]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Maryland==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! width=\"10%\" | Building\n! width=\"10%\" | Location\n! width=\"5%\" | Image\n! width=\"15%\" | Sculpture\n! width=\"10%\" | Sculptor\n! width=\"10%\" | Architect\n! width=\"5%\" | Installed\n! width=\"10%\" | Medium\n! width=\"25%\" | Notes\n|-\n|[[Maryland State House]] Annex\n|Maryland<br>State Circle,<br>[[Annapolis, Maryland|Annapolis]]\n|[[File:Maryland State House Porch (21601300955).jpg|100px]]\n|''[[Seal of Maryland]]''\n|\n|[[Baldwin & Pennington]]\n|1905\n|\n|[[File:Maryland State House from College Ave.JPG|100px|right]]The west portico and pediment were part of a 1902-05 expansion of the 1722 building.\n|-\n\n|[[Whitehall (Annapolis, Maryland)|Whitehall]]\n|Maryland<br>1915 Whitehall Road, [[Annapolis, Maryland|Annapolis]]\n|[[File:Whitehall, front (21413233360).jpg|100px]]\n|''Seal of Province of Maryland''<ref>[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=14D800P1488D0.2895&menu=search&aspect=Keyword&npp=50&ipp=20&spp=20&profile=ariall&ri=&term=&index=.GW&aspect=Keyword&term=&index=.AW&term=&in